<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><I>The short description:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in">A manager sends an employee to a
business trip. The employee receives notification. If the business
trip is local, the business process ends. If business trip type is
&ldquo;to another region&rdquo;, a human resource inspector receives
task &ldquo;make an official order&rdquo;. The employee receives task
&ldquo;sign an order&rdquo; and human resource inspector receives a
task &ldquo;receive a signature on the order&rdquo; concurrently.
Employee receives task &ldquo;receive a business trip warrant&rdquo;
and inspector receives a task &ldquo;give a business trip warrant&rdquo;.
Bookkeeper issues and employee receives the business trip money.
After employee returns from the business trip, employee submits and
bookkeeper receives the business trip financial report. The business
process ends.</P>
</BODY>
